-- Siemens May Face Gap of 14,000 Workers by 2020, CEO Tells BamS
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2012-03-11T12:28:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-11/siemens-may-face-gap-of-14-000-workers-by-2020-ceo-tells-bams.html
Siemens AG (SIE)  may face a shortfall of
as many as 14,000 employees by 2020 as  Germany  fails to produce
enough young skilled workers and engineers, Chief Executive
Officer  Peter Loescher  told  Bild am Sonntag  in an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
